A coding club tracks attendance at meetings. The Meeting class represents one meeting with a date string and the number of attendees. The AttendanceLog class stores a list of Meeting objects and supports analytic operations.

public class Meeting {
    private String date;
    private int attendees;

    public Meeting(String d, int a) { date = d; attendees = a; }
    public String getDate() { return date; }
    public int getAttendees() { return attendees; }
}

public class AttendanceLog {
    private ArrayList<Meeting> meetings;

    /** Builds the meetings list from parallel arrays. */
    public AttendanceLog(String[] dates, int[] counts) { /* part (a) */ }

    /** Returns an ArrayList<String> of dates whose attendance is strictly greater
     *  than the average attendance across all meetings stored. Must build a fresh
     *  AttendanceLog using the (String[], int[]) constructor written in part (a). */
    public static ArrayList<String> aboveAverageDates(String[] dates, int[] counts) { /* part (b) */ }
}

Precondition for part (a): dates and counts have the same length and length >= 1. No date is null.
Precondition for part (b): dates and counts have the same length and length >= 1.

frq_section.reference_solution:
import java.util.ArrayList;

public class Meeting {
    private String date;
    private int attendees;
    public Meeting(String d, int a) { date = d; attendees = a; }
    public String getDate() { return date; }
    public int getAttendees() { return attendees; }
}

class AttendanceLog {
    private ArrayList<Meeting> meetings;

    public AttendanceLog(String[] dates, int[] counts) {
        meetings = new ArrayList<Meeting>();
        for (int i = 0; i < dates.length; i++) {
            if (counts[i] >= 0) {
                meetings.add(new Meeting(dates[i], counts[i]));
            }
        }
    }

    public static ArrayList<String> aboveAverageDates(String[] dates, int[] counts) {
        AttendanceLog log = new AttendanceLog(dates, counts);
        ArrayList<String> result = new ArrayList<String>();
        if (log.meetings.size() == 0) {
            return result;
        }
        int total = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < log.meetings.size(); i++) {
            total += log.meetings.get(i).getAttendees();
        }
        double avg = (double) total / log.meetings.size();
        for (int i = 0; i < log.meetings.size(); i++) {
            if (log.meetings.get(i).getAttendees() > avg) {
                result.add(log.meetings.get(i).getDate());
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}

public class TemperatureGrid {
    private double[][] grid;
    private int days;
    private int cities;

    public TemperatureGrid(int days, int cities, double[] readings) {
        this.days = days;
        this.cities = cities;
        grid = new double[days][cities];
        for (int r = 0; r < days; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < cities; c++) {
                grid[r][c] = readings[r * cities + c];
            }
        }
    }

    public double cityAverage(int cityIndex) {
        double sum = 0.0;
        for (int r = 0; r < days; r++) {
            sum += grid[r][cityIndex];
        }
        return sum / days;
    }
}

